LAFIA – Dr Fatima Abdullahi, the ex-wife of the National Chairman of the ruling All Progressive Congress (APC), Senator Abdullahi Adanu, on Friday declared her intention to lock horns with governor Abdullahi Sule, at the party primary which is scheduled to hold on 18 of this month. Dr Fatima who declared her intention at the APC Secretariat in Lafia said what trigger her intention was to correct the wrong in the past. She explained that Nasarawa State is in dire need of a visionary, purposeful and competent leader who will build a robust socio-political and economic state. -Advertisement- According to Fatima, “My aspiration is borne out of my sincere concern that our state is in dire need of visionary, purposeful, competent and dynamic leadership that will build a robust socio-political-economic development realization of our dream of our founding fathers. “In the last decade I have reason to access the potential of the state. I have seen reason why I have to patake on the building of our dear state.“As a aggrerian state ,Agro value -chain that are bound in our state we will engage our teeming youth in agriculture sector that will effectively reduce our youth on the street. “Our teeming youth are die in abject poverty due to lack of proper planning to engage them in governance. We would assemble the best mind to run all-inclusive governance of the state. “When a doctor makes a mistake the patient dies, when a leader makes a mistake the entire nation perishes,” she said. She, however, noted that Nasarawa State is endowed with a lot of mineral resources which if properly harnessed would help reduce the jobless youths off the street.